text.tspan: Government Response Stringency Index vs. Biweekly change in confirmed
– The Government Response Stringency Index is a composite measure based on nine response indicators including school
closures, workplace closures, and travel bans, rescaled to a value from 0 to 100 (100 = strictest response).
– The biweekly growth rate on any given date measures the percentage change in the number of new confirmed cases over
the last 14 days relative to the number in the previous 14 days.
Source: Oxford COVID-19 Government Response Tracker, Blavatnik School of Government, University of Oxford – Last updated 14 December
2021, 21:08 (London time), Johns Hopkins University CSSE COVID-19 Data – Last updated 14 December, 21:05 (London time)
